body:
@bbende 
The interface org.apache.nifi.controller.ConfigurationContext doesn't have the method getStateManager like interface org.apache.nifi.reporting.ReportingContext. I figure out that org.apache.nifi.remote.client.SiteToSiteClient.Builder() must have a StateManager so config can create a PeerPersistence:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3923945/69368576-2afcad00-0c79-11ea-87cf-b09ae50ae566.png)

@belugabehr Thanks for your suggestion and in a concurrent environment it would be perfect.
In our case both `addMessage()` and `commitMessages()` are called from the same place and on the same thread: `ReportLineageToAtlas.consumeNiFiProvenanceEvents()`.
Although we could enhance it to support concurrent access as well, but `NiFiAtlasHook` explicitly declares itself as not being thread safe in its javadoc. That's why I would not add concurrency handling code to it and mix thread safe / non thread safe behaviours.

@mattyb149 was able to confirm that connection exceptions were not obscured by NullPointerException.  NiFi appeared to report true exception as expected.

+1

Will merge shortly
